law.text:
The governing boards of public senior higher education institutions shall, with respect to institutions under their jurisdiction:
Set education policy and adopt mission statements;
Establish goals that are consistent with the roles and missions approved for the institutions;
Select presidents;
Establish guidelines for admission standards that are consistent with the roles and missions approved for the institutions;
Set guidelines for tuition and mandatory fees;
Evaluate and approve short-range and long-range plans; and
Evaluate and approve institutional budget submissions.
